history.content:
Womxn in Mathematics is having 2 info sessions coming up, and we would love to have you there! You don't have to be a math major or even a womxn to join, just someone with interest in those subjects!

Womxn in Mathematics (WIM) is a club where UC Berkeley students interested in the field of Mathematics foster relationships and pursue academic success among like-minded individuals, with an emphasis on females and other underrepresented gender groups. Through professional and social events, we create and empower a strong community within the Math Department.

Founded in 2014, WIM has reached new heights with our events and reach within the math department. From Bob Ross De-Stress Paint nights to Career Workshops to Grad Panels, there is something here for you. We'd love to have you onboard - membership is low commitment and open to anyone.

Upcoming info sessions:

#1: Thursday, September 3rd, 6-7pm

Zoom: https://berkeley.zoom.us/j/7783198405

Facebook event: https://www.facebook.com/events/751671462291283/

#2: Wednesday, September 9th, 6-7pm

Zoom: https://berkeley.zoom.us/j/7783198405

Facebook event: https://www.facebook.com/events/228854131875331/

Learn more about us:
Facebook: www.facebook.com/WIMatUCB/
Instagram: @ucbwim
LinkedIn : https://www.linkedin.com/company/womxn-in-mathematics
Visit our website: www.wim.berkeley.edu
Join our Mailing List and Slack: https://tinyurl.com/WxM-2020
